claim.claim-text:
1. A structurally integrated biopsy system, comprising:
a single controller comprising a main computer module and a system input console, the system input console being communicatively coupled to the main computer module;
a tissue removal system communicatively coupled to the single controller, the tissue removal system including a tissue removal probe, a vacuum module, and a tissue removal control module, the tissue removal control module being coupled in communication with the main computer module, the tissue removal probe being communicatively coupled to the tissue removal control module;
an ultrasonic imaging system in direct physical connection with the tissue removal system, the ultrasonic imaging system communicatively coupled to the single controller, the ultrasonic imaging system including an ultrasonic imaging probe and an ultrasound control module, the ultrasound control module being coupled in communication with the main computer module, the ultrasonic imaging probe being coupled in communication with the ultrasonic control module;
an image display screen communicatively coupled to the single controller, the image display screen being configured to display an ultrasonic image display based upon data received from an ultrasound probe data and processed by the main computer module; and
the single controller being configured to both provide control information for the ultrasound control module of the ultrasonic imaging system and provide control information for the tissue removal control module of the tissue removal system in the structurally integrated biopsy system.

20. A structurally integrated biopsy system, comprising:
a movable base having wheels to facilitate movement of the structurally integrated biopsy system;
a tissue removal system mounted to the movable base, the tissue removal system including a probe connector configured to connect to a tissue removal probe;
an ultrasound imaging system directly connected to the tissue removal system, the ultrasound imaging system mounted to the movable base, the ultrasound imaging system being configured to generate an ultrasound image of a body region of a patient, and having an image display system having an image display screen to display ultrasound images taken by the ultrasound imaging system; and
a single controller mounted to the movable base, the single controller comprising a main computer module and an input console that are common to both the tissue removal system and the imaging system, the single controller being configured to be in communication with each of the tissue removal system and the ultrasound imaging system, the single controller being configured to both provide control information for the ultrasound imaging system and provide control information for the tissue removal system in the structurally integrated biopsy system, the input console including a single touch-display screen configured to operate both the tissue removal system and the imaging system.

38. A structurally integrated biopsy system, comprising:
a movable base having wheels to facilitate movement of the structurally integrated biopsy system;
a tissue removal system mounted to the movable base, the tissue removal system including a probe connector configured to connect to a tissue removal probe having control functionalities to obtain a tissue sample;
an ultrasound imaging system in direct physical connection with the tissue removal system, the ultrasonic imaging system mounted to the movable base, the ultrasound imaging system being configured to generate an ultrasound image of a body region of a patient, and having an image display system having an image display screen to display ultrasound images taken by the ultrasound imaging system; and
a single controller mounted to the movable base, the single controller comprising a main computer module and an input console that are common to both the tissue removal system and the imaging system,
the single controller being configured to be in communication with each of the tissue removal system and the ultrasound imaging system, the single controller being configured to provide in the structurally integrated biopsy system both control information for the ultrasound imaging system and control information for the control functionalities of the tissue removal probe of the tissue removal system.
